Figure 11(a,b) show the rectification factor R as a function of the temperature T1 of the thermal diode (Fig. 10) operating with a VO2 terminal made up of sample 1 or sample 2, respectively. The general increase of R with T1, within the MIT of both samples, is the result of the decrease of ϵ1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
